BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:1pjf-Xc7ykSA0j_nKku8E
SUMMARY:The Slide Rule
DTSTAMP:20260306T004550Z
DTSTART:20260305T190000Z
DESCRIPTION:The Slide Rule is a comics strip extravaganza where Seattle car
	toonists project their works on a screen and read them before a live audie
	nce!  \\n \\nMusic\\\, comedy\\\, drama and visual art combine in a unique
	ly entertaining artistic event. Hosted in the past at the former Hugo Hous
	e cafe\\\, The Slide Rule now returns to the new space\\\, featuring origi
	nal and classic material. Please join us for this panel-to-panel\\\, multi
	media happening! \\nThe Slide Rule is a group comics show\\\, hosted perio
	dically since the early 2000s by Davey Oil\\\, with contributions from oth
	er Seattle cartoonists and animators\\\, such as David Lasky\\\, Stefan Gr
	uber\\\, and Scott Faulkner.  \\nWhile the concept of live comic strip rea
	dings is not unique (New York's Carousel shows are another example) The Sl
	ide Rule is uniquely Seattle\\\, having been performed at the original Hug
	o House\\\, Crocodile Cafe and other mainstay art spaces\\\, with contribu
	tions from many Seattle cartoonists over the years.With a newly-burgeoning
	 cartoonist scene in town\\\, a renewed Slide Rule seeks to highlight this
	 vibrant art form in a city with a rich tradition of comics and live perfo
	rmance. \\n \\nReduced admission to this event is made possible with suppo
	rt from 4Culture.\n\nhttps://hugohouse.org/event/_2026-03-05/\n\nFrom Hugo
	 House
URL:https://hugohouse.org/event/_2026-03-05/
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:hugo-house
CATEGORIES:Hugo House
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
